Abstract

   The Neuro-Inspired Message Control Protocol (NIMCP) is a hybrid
   peer-to-peer communication protocol that models biological neural
   network behavior over TCP/IP networks. NIMCP implements concepts
   from neuroscience including spiking neurons, synaptic plasticity,
   excitation/inhibition, and emergent clustering while providing
   optional orchestration for network optimization. The protocol
   supports heterogeneous neural architectures, feature-based routing,
   and adaptive topology through local learning rules.

