Ethical weights updated through reinforcement:
ethical_weight += α * (social_reward - expected_value)


12. Orchestration Model

12.1 Orchestrator Role

Optional high-level controller that:
- Manages feature namespaces
- Sets global learning parameters
- Optimizes topology
- Monitors system health
- Provides semantic grounding

12.2 Orchestrator Messages

Example: Global learning rate adjustment
SET_LEARNING_RATE {
  target: "global" | ClusterID | NodeID,
  learning_rate: 0.01,
  effective_time: timestamp,
  duration: seconds
}

12.3 Autonomous vs Guided Operation

Networks can operate in three modes:
1. Fully autonomous - no orchestrator
2. Guided - orchestrator provides hints
3. Managed - orchestrator actively controls

